sharedPost.text:
Casting : "Maybe its love, maybe not"

I am Thomas Goersch from Stuttgart Germany. 
Actor and Filmdirector. 
I am making Independent Movies.
I present my movies on International Film festivals and was lucky to receive some awards. 
But the work is not about awards and money, its about making movies for the people to think about.
My next movie is a modern love story:
An elderly man is meeting another younger, very attractive man in the Internet.  But they are from different Continents. They start a long distance relastionship ship. which is full of passion and desire. 
One day the younger man starts to ask for money, cause he is a Student and no more able to pay his bills. 
The older man is full of distrust.
Is he only there  to pay his lovers bills or is there love between them ?
A story with two endings.
One with true love and one with only cheating. Based on a real story.
I am looking for the young attraktive Lover.
Men  25 to 42 years old,  good looking  who is able to film his parts on his own by smartshone
I am always open and honest. You can earn no money on this. but maybe there is a good film in the end promoting for you.
I guess its not necessary that an educated actor is playing this part. so feel free to get in touch
Thats me 
www.imdb.com/name/nm1591928
Get in touch under Thomas.Goersch@vodafonemail.de 
please ask for details.

UNPAID CASTING CALL FOR MISUNDERSTOOD (TRAILER CONCEPT)
Directed by Michael Helm 

📍Shooting Location: Provo, Utah.

Interested? Email carsonvirgin.films@gmail.com for sides!

Auditions are held via Self-tapes due by February 18th @ midnight 

Looking for multiple actors 

- Amy (female | ages 14-22) !!Must be comfortable riding a bike!! Amy is a goth, independent teen whose buried guilt over her little brother’s tragic death resurfaces, sending her into impulsive decisions that turn her world upside down

-Marly (female | ages 30-50) a fiercely independent and caring woman who works two jobs to raise her traumatized Niece as her own, helping her heal while fighting tirelessly to protect the small family they’ve built together.

-Wayne (male | ages 40-60) is the new principal of Montana High determined to correct his students’ behavior, but as he learns the history behind Amy’s struggles, his stern resolve is guided by compassion and understanding.

- Joanie (female | ages 35-60) is Amy’s longtime Therapist who, despite once helping her make great progress, has grown proud and self-absorbed - hiding behind a caring facade as she becomes increasingly dismissive of Amy’s struggles 

ALSO LOOKING FOR THE FOLLOWING NON SPEAKING ACTORS:

Amy’s deceased brother (5)

Amy’s mom (35-55)

Biker boy (10)

Actor/Singer/Costume Designer available for work.
• I’ve worked on movies and shows like ‘The Hunting Wives’ (currently filming) ‘Please Don’t Destroy’, I’m the star of ‘Midnight Cabaret’ and I’ve done some reality TV.

• I’ve contributed music for the soundtracks of ‘The Bad Girls Club’ ‘Welcome To New York’ and ‘Midnight Cabaret’.

• I’ve designed costumes for shows like ‘Doom Patrol’ on HBO, ‘RuPauls Drag Race’, ‘Claws’ on TNT, ‘Dragula’ on AMC, ‘Queen Of Drag’ and a few others.

I’m currently based in Charlotte NC and looking for speaking role acting work, background acting work, soundtrack work or costume design work on film, TV shows or independent features as well.

I can be reached by message or email at: BrandonHiltonReal@gmail.com

My IMDb resume -

🎬 CASTING CALL – PAID PRINCIPAL ROLES 

(ATLANTA LOCAL HIRE)

CORRUPTION OFFICER – Non-Union Pilot Episode

📍 Atlanta, GA

📅 February 18, 2026 (One-Day Shoot | 4–5 Hours)

💵 Paid Principal Day Rate | Non-Union | Independent Production

Production is casting two (2) East Asian male actors for a gritty, character-driven pilot set inside a correctional facility. 

These are performance-forward roles requiring strong physical presence, emotional control, and compelling nonverbal acting.

**CHEN (22–32)**

Male, East Asian, lean build

Older brother

Controlled, observant, strategic

Minimal dialogue

Must convey internal power and authority through stillness

Portrays an incarcerated individual

**JIN (20–30)**

Male, East Asian, lean/athletic build

Younger brother

Intense yet disciplined

Strong physical performer

Comfortable with choreographed fight sequences

Portrays an incarcerated individual

Both Roles:
* Physical performance with choreographed fight sequences (no high-risk stunts)
* Martial arts or movement training a plus
* Mandarin or Cantonese ability a plus (brief dialogue)
* Must be comfortable portraying incarcerated characters
* Atlanta local hire only

This project emphasizes physical storytelling and screen presence. 

We are seeking actors who can command attention with minimal dialogue and controlled intensity.

📩 TO SUBMIT:

Email:** info.coshort@gmail.com**

Subject Line: ROLE: CHEN or ROLE: JIN

Please include:
* Headshot
* Full-body photo
* Resume (if available)
* Acting reel or short clip
* Relevant physical or stunt experience

Serious inquiries only. Thank you.

#AtlantaActors #ATLcasting #CastingCall #AsianActors #EastAsianActors #IndieFilm #NonUnionActors

items.text: My friends and I are shooting a short film at Stone Circle Theater in Ridgewood, Queens on Monday, 2/16, Presidents’ Day. We are looking for extras to play wedding guests. Cstoddard@quailbell.com. You can watch other samples of our work online: “5 Ways I Didn’t Marry You” and “Don’t Mind If I Don’t.”
